channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Dueling Debate Prep: Biden to Go Into Hiding, Trump Stays Out in the Field
'Unethical': California sheriff rips Dems for plotting 'immoral' move to sink anti-crime proposal
item.description: A California sheriff told Fox News Digital that Democrats in his state are trying to sabotage a bipartisan crime fix on the ballot in November for ideological reasons.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Oversight Probes NewsGuard's Methods
item.description: Republicans on the House Oversight Committee, who have launched an investigation into NewsGuard, a news ratings service, want to know what criteria the company uses while determining which news networks are telling the truth and which are not, committee Chairman Rep. James ...

item.title: US Marine Veteran Dies Alone, but Not Forgotten
Trump motions to have judge in New York civil fraud case recused
item.description: Lawyers for former President Donald Trump have filed a new motion in his New York civil fraud case alleging that the judge engaged in "prohibited communications" and should recuse himself.

item.title: Trump Gets Last Word at CNN Debate With Biden
item.description: A coin flip guaranteed former President Donald Trump will get the last word at a June 27 debate on CNN with President Joe Biden.

item.title: Gavin Newsom Gets a Big Win, Screws Over 'Democracy'
FBI raids home connected to Oakland Mayor Sheng Thao day after recall effort qualifies for ballot
item.description: The FBI on Thursday raided a home connected to Oakland Mayor Sheng Thao. This after a recall campaign to oust her received enough signatures to qualify for November.

item.title: Emerson Poll: Trump Maintains Lead Over Biden in Swing States
item.description: Former President Donald Trump continues to lead President Joe Biden in key swing states, according to a new poll from Emerson College Polling/The Hill.

item.title: Northeast Liberal Arts College Slammed by Declining Enrollment Due to Pro-Hamas Protests—Media to Blame?
Biden admin won't say whether it plans to contact family of Maryland mom allegedly killed by illegal immigrant
item.description: The Biden administration will not say whether it plans to reach out to the family of Rachel Morin, a Maryland mom who was allegedly murdered by an illegal immigrant last year.

item.title: Biden Loses Support Among Women Voters
item.description: President Joe Biden's lead among female voters has waned since the 2020 election and is smaller than former President Donald Trump's support among male voters, according to an average of more than 30 polls conducted during the last six months and compiled by The New York Times.

item.title: FBI Raids Oakland Mayor Sheng Thao's Residence—Authorities Mum on Reason Why
Progressive mayor challenges rival to name 'three drag queens' in city: 'redeem yourself'
item.description: At a recent debate, San Francisco Mayor London Breed challenged rival Mark Farrell to name three city drag queens to prove his appreciation for the city's LGBT community.

item.title: Gov. Burgum 'Very Worried' About Another 9/11
item.description: Gov. Doug Burgum, R-N.D., says he's worried about another 9/11-type attack in the U.S. after more than three years of President Joe Biden's southern border policies. Burgum, who reportedly is on former President Donald Trump's shortlist to fill the vice-presidential spot on ...
